cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.DC, cs.PF, cs.PL

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category as it proposes a design and implementation of a priority queue. It may also belong to cs.DB (Databases) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as it discusses the use of external memory and parallelization. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.PF (Performance) and cs.PL (Programming Languages) as it focuses on achieving higher performance through parallelization and the use of the STXXL library.
